OL,6,FPurple plaques are dedicated to women
OL,7,Fwho have made an impact in Wales and
OL,8,Fbeyond, and aim to "shine a light on
OL,9,Fwomen's achievements by improving the
OL,10,Frecognition of remarkable women in
OL,11,FWales."
OL,13,FOne of the people who came out to
OL,14,Fsupport the unveiling of the plaque
OL,15,Fwas BSL teacher David Duller.
OL,17,FHe said it was Dorothy who encouraged
OL,18,Fhim to study sign language and become
OL,19,Fa teacher.
